== Overview == Initially constructed during the {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the tumulus was later dismantled and reconstructed, making it a unique example among kofun structures<ref name="bunkazai">Uehara Archaeological Investigation Report (Tsukaan Kofun), Kawachinagano City Board of Education, 1998.</ref>.
Excavations by the Kawachinagano City Board of Education revealed cremated human remains inside a jar, alongside pottery, ceramics, and coins such as {{ill|Yongle Tongbao|ja|永楽通宝|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kan'ei Tsūhō|ja|寛永通宝|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Inscriptions on nearby stone pagodas and burial goods suggest that the chamber was reassembled during the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and repurposed as a burial site<ref name="bunkazai" />.
