{{Infobox ancient site|type = {{ill|Round Kofun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|qq=}} |name = Tsukaan Kofun |image = [[File:塚穴古墳 (河内長野市)１.jpg|280px]] |caption = Full view of Tsukaan Kofun |alternate_name = |group = |location = [[:en:Kawachinagano|Kawachinagano]], {{ill|Uehara Nishimachi|ja|長野地区 (河内長野市)#上原西町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uehara Nishimachi|qq=}} 19, Osaka Prefecture |coordinates = |coordinates = |coordinates = |coordinates = |coordinates = |coordinates = |iso = |type = {{ill|Circular tumulus|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Circular tumulus|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|qq=}} |size = Approx. 15 m (current state) |burial = {{ill|Yokoana-style stone chamber|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokoana-style stone chamber|13=User:Immanuelle/Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=}} |burial goods = |accompanying = |period = Unknown |buried = Unknown (possibly {{ill|Takamu no Ō|ja|高向王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamu no Ō|qq=}}<ref name="sankei" />) |heritage = |cultural = |site_no = |remarks = Reconstructed during the early modern period |map = |map = |type = |map_dot_label = |map_dot_label = }}
'''Tsukaana Kofun''' (塚穴古墳) is a [[:en:Kofun|Kofun]] located in [[:en:Kawachinagano|Kawachinagano]], {{ill|Uehara Nishimachi|ja|長野地区 (河内長野市)#上原西町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uehara Nishimachi|qq=}}, Osaka Prefecture. It is currently shaped as a {{ill|circular tumulus|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/circular tumulus|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|qq=}}.
== Overview == Initially constructed during the [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]], the tumulus was later dismantled and reconstructed, making it a unique example among kofun structures<ref name="bunkazai">Uehara Archaeological Investigation Report (Tsukaan Kofun), Kawachinagano City Board of Education, 1998.</ref>.
Excavations by the Kawachinagano City Board of Education revealed cremated human remains inside a jar, alongside pottery, ceramics, and coins such as [[:en:Yongle Tongbao|Yongle Tongbao]] and [[:en:Kan'ei Tsūhō|Kan'ei Tsūhō]]. Inscriptions on nearby stone pagodas and burial goods suggest that the chamber was reassembled during the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]] and repurposed as a burial site<ref name="bunkazai" />.
== Legend == Local folklore recounts that the tumulus was dismantled during the construction of [[:en:Osaka Castle|Osaka Castle]] under [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] to procure stones. It is said that attempts to move the large stones caused "supernatural events," leading workers to reconstruct the chamber in its original type<ref name="sankei">{{Cite news|lang=ja|url=https://www.sankei.com/article/20170923-7OVK3BYOH5NBJMWGG2NYLQ7JHY/|title=Attempts to uncover the contents led to disasters? The strange legend of Tsukaan Kofun|newspaper=Sankei News|publisher=Sankei Digital|date=September 13, 2017|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20240422030830/https://www.sankei.com/article/20170923-7OVK3BYOH5NBJMWGG2NYLQ7JHY/|archivedate=April 22, 2024}}</ref>. Wedge marks on the stones confirm attempts to split them during dismantling.
== References == * Uehara Archaeological Investigation Report (Tsukaan Kofun), Kawachinagano City Board of Education, 1998. * ''Kawachinagano City History,'' Vol. 1, 1994.<ref name="sankei" /> * Local intypeational signboard, Uehara Property District, 1997.
